{
  "texts": [
    "Segal et al. (2021) introduced an approach to synthesizing clinically realistic chest X-rays using progressively growing Generative Adversarial Networks (PGGANs), allowing for multi-modal sampling with minimal computational cost.",
    "By employing latent class optimization, the model efficiently generated diverse synthetic images for each labeled class.",
    "Paleontologists can use this approach to generate realistic samples for a wide range of minority fossil classes by leveraging latent class optimizations within modern GAN frameworks.",
    "GANs have also been employed to enhance medical images, for detail enhancement, or to create new artworks by learning and mimicking the styles of various artists, demonstrating their ability to generate complex outputs.",
    "For instance, GANs have enhanced medical images by filling in missing details, improving resolution, and removing noise."
  ]
}